of the COVID-19 updates. We are aware that many students may be impacted as further developments are announced. Although U&I Care is faced with limited resources, we hope to support all students in need. Upon completing your application for the emergency fund, we ask that you understand that many students of your fellow students are experiencing similar financial hardship s as we navigate these uncertain times. Please be mindful of your financial request and provide documentation to support any requests made. We encourage students to contact the Office of Financial Aid and Scholarships prior to submitting your application to ensure you have utilized any and all aid awarded to you for the 20 19/2020 academic year.  Thank you for your patience at this  time.  Please take care and stay safe.          U & I Care Fund   The U and I Care Emergency Fund is made possible through the partnership between the Office of the Dean of Students & Office of Student Financial Aid and Scholarships. The U and I Care Fund provides temporary, short-term financial assistance  to currently enrolled students who are unable to meet essential expenses due to a temporary or unexpected hardship. This emergency funding program is designed to offer financial assistance to students in the form of one-time awards (typically not exceeding $500) . Emergency funding is NOT intended to provide ongoing relief for recurring expenses. Decisions regarding disbursement of funds are made on a case-by-case basis.       Accordion     Types of Expenses Considered         Types of Expenses Considered    Overdue rent and utilities (i.e. eviction notice, utility disconnection notice)  Medical, dental, or mental health emergencies  Books, school supplies, or other school related expenses  Replacement of belongings lost in a fire or natural disaster  Safety related needs (i.e. changing locks, short term emergency shelter)  Travel related to the death of an immediate family member         Expenses Generally Not Covered         Expenses Generally Not Covered    Tuition and fees  Campus Housing costs  Health insurance  Credit card expenses  Parking tickets and other fines  Costs for entertainment, recreation, and non-emergency travel  Other non-essential expenses (i.e. cable bill, cell phone bill)              U & I Care Emergency Fund   To find more information about the U and I Care Emergency Fund, eligibility requirements, and how to apply, visit the online application .      How to Give?  A gift can be made online          Assistance    Back to main content           Academic Concerns     Academic Resources    Academic Grievances    Withdrawal    Emergencies and Absences      Health & Personal Concerns     Hospitalization & Emergencies    Mental Health    Victims of Crime and Safety Concerns    Housing Instability & Food Insecurity    Financial Concerns    Cannabis: Know the Facts      Campus Life    Faculty & Staff Resources     The Student Response Team    Behavioral Response Intervention Team      U & I Care     Meet Our Partners    Care Facts    News & Events    U & I Care Fund    U & I Care Plan                    UIC Logo        Office of the Dean of Students         DOS Offices    Career Services    Student Employment    Counseling Center    Wellness Center      For Employees    SA Human Resources    SA Technology    Leave Management    The Pulse      Safety    UIC Police    Office of Access & Equity    Contact-US    Giving         Contact   1200 West Harrison St., 3030 SSB Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-4857  dos@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield  